					<p>
					</p>

					<p>
						Moon Dunchin is a professor of mathematics at Tufts University in Massachusetts.
						She has become known as a leading expert in gerrymandering and has made it her goal to use education to combat its use and protect voting rights.
						She directs the Metric Geometry and Gerrymandering Group (MGGG), whose goal is to research and share with the general public tools for better understanding the impact of districting, and provide consulting services.
					</p>
