				<title>Ranthony A.C.
				Edmonds</title>
				<sidebyside widths="25% 2% 73%">
					<image source="edmonds-pic.png"/>
						<p>
						</p>

						<p>
							Ranthony Edmonds is currently an Assistant Research Professor at Duke University.
							Edmonds works to increase opportunities for Black Americans and other members of other marginalized groups to pursue careers in the mathematical sciences.
							In the summer of 2021 she was part of a large grassroots effort across multiple states to use mathematics and data science to address fair representation, with a particular focus on utilizing public input on communities of interest for consideration during the 2021 redistricting process.
							Recently she was awarded an inaugural NSF Ascending Postdoctoral Fellowship to study applications of topological data analysis to redistricting.
						</p>
